The trio of Sparta Rotterdam goalkeeper Maduka Okoye, Nantes forward Moses Simon and Porto defender Zaidu Sanusi are the latest players to arrive at the Super Eagles camp as the preparation for the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations continues. Simon arrived alongside Sanusi on Saturday night while Okoye arrived yesterday evening to bring the number of players now present in the Super Eagles camp at the Bolton White Hotel, Abuja to 13. Both players, especially the Nantes attacker, are expected to play a key role in Nigeria’s quest for a fourth AFCON title. This was after the arrival of Chidozie Awaziem (Alanyaspor), Francis Uzoho (Omonia), Henry Onyekuru (Olympiacos), and Peter Olayinka (Slavia Praha). The other six players already in camp include Chidera Ejuke (CSKA Moscow), Daniel Akpeyi (Kaizer Chiefs), Sadiq Umar (Almeria), Olisa Ndah (Orlando Pirates), John Noble (Enyimba FC) and Taiwo Awoniyi (Union Berlin).   Osimhen disappointed to miss AFCON but will be there…     Gbajabiamila to face chess champion in friendly game     PSG’s Messi, three others test positive for COVID-19   No fewer than 15 more players are still being expected in the Super Eagles camp ahead of the 2021 AFCON with the first training expected to commence at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium yesterday. - Advertisement - Other players still being expected include Leicester duo Kelechi Iheanacho and Wilfred Ndidi, Alex Iwobi (Everton), Semi Ajayi (West Brom); William Ekong (Watford) and Frank Onyeka of Brentford FC. Olaoluwa Aina (Torino); Jamilu Collins (Paderborn); Tyrone Ebuehi (Venezia); Zaidu Sanusi (Porto); Kelechi Nwakali (Huesca) and Kenneth Omeruo (Leganes) are also expected to be at the camp. The others are Odion Ighalo of Al-Shabab Riyadh, Samuel Chukwueze (Villarreal FC, Spain), Ahmed Musa (Fatih Karagümrük), and Joe Aribo (Glasgow Rangers).